File: Eskom warns its systems remain vulnerable. JOHANNESBURG - Embattled power utility Eskom is keeping the lights on, for now. Eskom says it will not be implementing load-shedding on Thursday as it has managed to return some of its generating units. READ: Eskom not expecting load-shedding this weekend The Majuba power station in Mpumalanga caught fire on Wednesday but was later restored. Eskom says the power station still has a stock level of 50 days. Investigations into the blaze will only begin once the facility has cooled down. READ: Fire at Majuba power station extinguished Eskom warns its systems remain vulnerable and that load-shedding could be implemented if there are changes to the system. Consumers have been urged to continue to use electricity sparingly.